ich will review and decide on the PR/issue."}, {"id": 67766349, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2Nzc2NjM0OQ==", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/E-mentor", "name": "E-mentor", "color": "02E10C", "default": false, "description": "Call for participation: This issue has a mentor. Use RustcContributor::new on Zulip for discussion."}, {"id": 419557634, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw0MTk1NTc2MzQ=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/E-medium", "name": "E-medium", "color": "02e10c", "default": false, "description": "Call for participation: Experience needed to fix: Medium / intermediate"}, {"id": 630799571, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2MzA3OTk1NzE=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/I-compilemem", "name": "I-compilemem", "color": "e10c02", "default": false, "description": "Problems and improvements with respect to memory usage during compilation."}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": {"login": "tdelabro", "id": 34384633, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM0Mzg0NjMz", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/34384633?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro", "html_url": "https://github.com/tdelabro", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "assignees": [{"login": "tdelabro", "id": 34384633, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM0Mzg0NjMz", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/34384633?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro", "html_url": "https://github.com/tdelabro", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tdelabro/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}], "milestone": null, "comments": 5, "created_at": "2021-04-18T15:23:33Z", "updated_at": "2021-04-23T19:36:45Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "This is a special case of https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/76382. `Attributes` is 72 bytes large and used in quite a few places:\r\n\r\n- [`Item::attrs`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/nightly-rustc/rustdoc/clean/types/struct.Item.html#structfield.attrs)\r\n- [`FnDecl::attrs`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/nightly-rustc/rustdoc/clean/types/struct.FnDecl.html#structfield.attrs)\r\n- [`ExternalCrate::attrs`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/nightly-rustc/rustdoc/clean/types/struct.ExternalCrate.html#structfield.attrs)\r\n\r\nThis has two downsides:\r\n1. Attributes takes up a lot of space in memory, so this bloats memory usage\r\n2. It means attributes have to calculated ahead of time, instead of on-demand. In particular, this requires adding a new attrs field whenever `render` needs to look at the attrs of a specific `clean` type (https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/83900#discussion_r615363572).\r\n\r\nIt would be better to calculate this on-demand, so it uses less memory and doesn't have to be calculated for each and every item.\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_START -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_START -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_DATA_START$${\"user\":\"tdelabro\"}$$TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_DATA_END -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_END -->\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_END -->", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/84304/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/84304/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}